Mixing / Blending method: PMMA impregnated into the amorphous phase of PP in situ polymn.
Name: poly(prop-1-ene)//poly(methyl methacrylate)
Polymerization information:
Reactant: MMA
Type: addition
Mechanism: radical
Style: solution polymn.
Solvent: supercritical CO2 (scCO2)
Initiator: AIBN
Additives: PP plate (20*20*0.5mm)
Condition: PP substrate soaked in pressurized scCO2 containing MMA/AIBN mixt. for 1h at 35C, MMA impregnated in the amorphous phase of PP and subsequently in situ polymd. at 80C for 24h, initial pressure of CO2=ca.4.7MPa
Post-treatment: Obtained PP/PMMA composite extd. with acetone for 24h using Soxhlet extractor, then dried in vacuo at RT
Polymn. remarks: Radical-initiated in situ polymn.
Processing information: Shape of Test Piece: Sheet
['Glass transition temp. ca 130 [C]', 'Method: DMA', 'Condition: Heating rate;5C/min&Frequency;10Hz&Tensile mode', 'Remarks: Tg of PMMA phase, temp. of tan(delta)peak, taken from the Fig.12']

Post-treatment: Culture broth centrifuged at 4C for 1h and washed, Soxhlet extd. with CHCl3 at 80C, then CHCl3 evapd. from the extract (P1+P2)

As polymerized
